It appears to be a bunch of fine "steel wool" that is actually copper or
bronze in color.  I pulled it out of a rusting filter and it can be
gunked up with carbon also.  Perhaps one could use copper "brillo" style
pads and stuff them into a box welded in line with the EGR inlet to the
intake??


